snippet.title: Teen dies after herding bulls on WA farm
snippet.content: A 19-year-old woman has died after being crushed by a bull at a farm near Esperance in Western Australia's south. A co-worker found the unconscious victim at about 11.30am on Monday and she was rushed by ambulance to Esperance Hospital where she died a short time later. Worksafe will investigate and a report is being prepared for the coroner. (C) AAP 2017
